<span id="ix.v.iv-p2"></span>Addæus <span
id="fr_2947"></span>[2948](#fn_2947.md) preached at Edessa and in
Mesopotamia (he was from Paneus <span
id="fr_2948"></span>[2949](#fn_2948) .md) in the days of Abgar the king. 
And, when he was among the Zophenians, Severus the son of Abgar sent and
slew him at Agel Hasna, as also a young man his disciple.

